 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Syth<note type="tnote-indicator" n="1">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="1">G</note> that ye lyste<note type="gloss-indicator" n="2">G</note> to be my hostesse,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="2">T</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="1">Since</gloss><gloss n="2"> desire</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And in youre book to set myne image,<note type="enote-indicator" n="1">N</note> <note type="tnote-indicator" n="3">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="3">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="3">my image</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Wake and remembre wyth grete avyses<note type="tnote-indicator" n="4">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="4">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="4">much consideration</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Howe my custome and mortall<note type="tnote-indicator" n="5">T</note>  usage<note type="enote-indicator" n="2">N</note> </l><l><milestone n="5" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Ys for to spare<note type="tnote-indicator" n="6">T</note>  nether<note type="tnote-indicator" n="7">T</note>  olde ne<note type="tnote-indicator" n="8">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="5">G</note> yonge of age,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="5">nor</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>But that ye nowe in thys world levyng<note type="gloss-indicator" n="6">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="6">living</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Afore<note type="tnote-indicator" n="9">T</note>  be redy, or<note type="gloss-indicator" n="7">G</note> I my belle<note type="enote-indicator" n="3">N</note>  rynge.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="7">Be ready in advance, lest</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>My dredefull spere<note type="gloss-indicator" n="8">G</note> full<note type="gloss-indicator" n="9">G</note> sharpe ygrounde,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="10">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="10">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="8">spear</gloss><gloss n="9"> very</gloss><gloss n="10"> honed</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Doth yow<note type="gloss-indicator" n="11">G</note> now lo here thys<note type="tnote-indicator" n="11">T</note>  manace:<note type="gloss-indicator" n="12">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="11">you</gloss><gloss n="12">threaten</gloss></l><l><milestone n="10" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Armoure ys noonne<note type="gloss-indicator" n="13">G</note> that may withstande<note type="tnote-indicator" n="12">T</note>  hys wounde,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="13">There is no armor</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Ne whomme I merke,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="13">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="14">G</note> ther ys non other<note type="tnote-indicator" n="14">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="15">G</note> grace<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="14">whom I mark</gloss><gloss n="15"> no other</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>To fynde respite<note type="gloss-indicator" n="16">G</note> of day, oure, ne space;<note type="tnote-indicator" n="15">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="17">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="16">reprieve</gloss><gloss n="17"> brief while</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Wherfore<note type="gloss-indicator" n="18">G</note> be redy and have no dysdeyne,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="19">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="18">Therefore</gloss><gloss n="19"> take no offence</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Yef<note type="tnote-indicator" n="16">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="20">G</note> of my commyng, the tyme be uncerteyne.<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="20">Although</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><milestone n="15" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Remembre, youre yeres almost past<note type="tnote-indicator" n="17">T</note>  be;</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Of flowryng age<note type="gloss-indicator" n="21">G</note> lasteth but<note type="tnote-indicator" n="18">T</note>  a seasoun;<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="21">age of flourishing (i.e., youth)</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>By procese at ey<note type="tnote-indicator" n="19">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="22">G</note> men may see<space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="22">In due course with their own eyes</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Beauté declyneth, hys blossom falleth<note type="tnote-indicator" n="20">T</note>  doune.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="23">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="23">falls down</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And lytyll and lytyll by successioun<note type="gloss-indicator" n="24">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="24">by degrees</gloss></l><l><milestone n="20" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Cometh croked elde<note type="gloss-indicator" n="25">G</note> unwarly<note type="gloss-indicator" n="26">G</note> crepyng,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="21">T</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="25">old age</gloss><gloss n="26">unexpectedly</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>With hys patent<note type="enote-indicator" n="4">N</note>  purely thanne<note type="tnote-indicator" n="22">T</note>  manysshyng.<note target="#1" type="footnotelink">1</note></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>The gospell byddeth than<note type="gloss-indicator" n="27">G</note> wake and pray,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="23">T</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="27">bids them</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>For of my commyng there is no tyme sette;<note type="enote-indicator" n="5">N</note> </l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Ne no manne knoweth<note type="gloss-indicator" n="28">G</note> whenne<note type="tnote-indicator" n="24">T</note>  he shall dye,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="25">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="29">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="28">knows</gloss><gloss n="29"> die</gloss></l><l><milestone n="25" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Ne agayne myne entré<note type="gloss-indicator" n="30">G</note> no gate may be shutte;<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="30">against my entry</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Twene<note type="gloss-indicator" n="31">G</note> me and kynde<note type="tnote-indicator" n="26">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="32">G</note> there is a knot unknyt,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="27">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="33">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="31">Between</gloss><gloss n="32"> creation</gloss><gloss n="33"> loosened</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>That in thys worlde every<note type="tnote-indicator" n="28">T</note>  lyvyng<note type="gloss-indicator" n="34">G</note> creature<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="34">living</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>For<note type="tnote-indicator" n="29">T</note>  <persName>Adams</persName><note type="tnote-indicator" n="30">T</note>  synne<note type="enote-indicator" n="6">N</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="35">G</note> must dye of nature.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="36">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="35">sin</gloss><gloss n="36"> naturally</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg type="rubric"><l>Thyese balades that thus ben wrytenne<note target="#2" type="footnotelink">2</note> here be tak<note target="#3" type="footnotelink">3</note> owte of the book of <persName>Johnne Lucas</persName><note type="enote-indicator" n="7">N</note>  and sayde to the peple that shall see thys lytell tretyse in tyme to come.<note type="tnote-indicator" n="31">T</note> </l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>O worldely<note type="tnote-indicator" n="32">T</note>  folke, averteth and take hede<note type="gloss-indicator" n="37">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="37">take notice</gloss></l><l><milestone n="30" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>What vengeaunce and punicyoun<note type="gloss-indicator" n="38">G</note><space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="38">punishment</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/><persName>God</persName> shall take after ye be<note type="tnote-indicator" n="33">T</note>  dede<note type="gloss-indicator" n="39">G</note><space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="39">you are dead</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>For youre trespas and youre transgressioun,</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Whiche breke<note type="tnote-indicator" n="34">T</note>  his preceptys<note type="tnote-indicator" n="35">T</note>  ayenst<note type="tnote-indicator" n="36">T</note>  al reasoun;<note type="gloss-indicator" n="40">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="40">against all reason</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Ye have foryete<note type="gloss-indicator" n="41">G</note> how with his precious bloode,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="42">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="41">have forgotten</gloss><gloss n="42"> blood</gloss></l><l><milestone n="35" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Yow for to save,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="43">G</note> he dyed<note type="tnote-indicator" n="37">T</note>  onne the Roode.<note type="gloss-indicator" n="44">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="43">In order to save you</gloss><gloss n="44"> the Cross</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Lerne for to dye and hate<note type="tnote-indicator" n="38">T</note>  for to lye;<note type="gloss-indicator" n="45">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="45">hate to live [in sin]</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Of olde offens<note type="tnote-indicator" n="39">T</note>  amonge<note type="gloss-indicator" n="46">G</note> have repentaunce;<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="46">sins constantly</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And, to eschewe al scorne and mokry<note type="tnote-indicator" n="40">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="47">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="47">mockery</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Ayenst<note type="tnote-indicator" n="41">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="48">G</note> vyces, do<note type="tnote-indicator" n="42">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="49">G</note> almes<note type="enote-indicator" n="8">N</note>  and penaunce,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="48">Against</gloss><gloss n="49"> do (perform)</gloss></l><l><milestone n="40" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>And for to have<note type="tnote-indicator" n="43">T</note>  moste souveranly<note type="tnote-indicator" n="44">T</note>  plesaunce<note type="gloss-indicator" n="50">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="50">highest pleasure</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>To sewe<note type="gloss-indicator" n="51">G</note> the pathes of oure lorde <persName>Jhesu</persName>,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="51">show (reveal)</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Trewe exampeleré<note type="tnote-indicator" n="45">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="52">G</note> of grace and vertew,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="53">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="52">True exemplar</gloss><gloss n="53"> virtue</gloss></l></lg>
 <lg><l><space rend="indent1"/>Whyche<note type="gloss-indicator" n="54">G</note> for oure sake and oure redempcioun<note type="tnote-indicator" n="46">T</note> <space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="54">Who</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And for oure love was nayled to<note type="tnote-indicator" n="47">T</note>  a tre,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="55">G</note><space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="55">tree (i.e., the Cross)</gloss></l><l><milestone n="45" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Suffred<note type="tnote-indicator" n="48">T</note>  payne<note type="gloss-indicator" n="56">G</note> and passioun,<note type="tnote-indicator" n="49">T</note> <space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="56">pain</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And nothyng asketh<note type="tnote-indicator" n="50">T</note>  of hygh ne lowe degree</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Recompensed ayenwarde<note type="tnote-indicator" n="51">T</note>  for to be,</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>But that we sette<note type="tnote-indicator" n="52">T</note>  all holy<note type="tnote-indicator" n="53">T</note>  oure ententes</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>For to fulfyll Hys commaundmentys.<note target="#4" type="footnotelink">4</note></l></lg>
 <lg><l><milestone n="50" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>Wherby menne may, that prudent be and wyse,</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>The joyes clayme,<note type="gloss-indicator" n="57">G</note> whiche be eternall,<space rend="indent1"/><gloss n="57">claim the joys</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>And entré<note type="tnote-indicator" n="54">T</note> <note type="gloss-indicator" n="58">G</note> in to paradyse,<space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="58">again</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>From<note type="tnote-indicator" n="55">T</note>  whens<note type="gloss-indicator" n="59">G</note> <persName>Adam</persName> had a fall;<space rend="indent2"/><gloss n="59">whence</gloss></l><l><space rend="indent1"/>To whyche place above celestiall</l><l><milestone n="55" unit="line"/><space rend="indent1"/>O <persName>Cryste Jhesu</persName>, so brynge<note type="tnote-indicator" n="56">T</note>  us to that glory,</l><l><space rend="indent1"/>Whyche by thy dethe<note type="tnote-indicator" n="57">T</note>  had the victory. Amen.<note type="tnote-indicator" n="58">T</note> </l></lg>
 
